{"id":"/questions//questions/2649193.json.json", "creationDate":"2010-04-15T21:45:04.617", "body":"\n\nI have this configuration in `ibatis-config.xml`\n\n\t<configuration>\n\t    <properties resource=\"collector.properties\"/>\n\t    <environments default=\"development\">\n\t        <environment id=\"development\">\n\t            <transactionManager type=\"JDBC\" />\n\t            <dataSource type=\"POOLED\">\n\t                <property name=\"driver\" value=\"${dev.jdbc.driver}\" />\n\t                <property name=\"url\" value=\"${dev.jdbc.url}\" />\n\t            </dataSource>\n\t        </environment>\n\t        <environment id=\"test\">\n\t            <transactionManager type=\"JDBC\" />\n\t            <dataSource type=\"POOLED\">\n\t                <property name=\"driver\" value=\"${test.jdbc.driver}\" />\n\t                <property name=\"url\" value=\"${test.jdbc.url}\" />\n\t            </dataSource>\n\t        </environment>\n\t    </environments>\n\t    <mappers>\n\t    </mappers>\n\t</configuration>\n\t\n\nAs shown it will load datasource from `<environment id=\"development\">`\n\n<b>QUESTION</b>: Is it possible at run time switch to use `<environment id=\"test\">` without modifying XML? For example - I have a test file where I'm using `SqlSessionFactory` and want to set it programmatically to use test environment?", "lastActivityDate":"2011-03-08T15:51:42.540", "title":"iBatis - select environment using XML", "tags":[["environment"], ["ibatis"], ["xml-configuration"]], "docScore":0, "comments":[], "answers":[], "creationYearMonth":"201004", "itemTally":0, "owner":null}